  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Improving effectiveness through communications</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Feed the Minds works with partners in Africa and Asia to promote literacy through grass-roots development programmes covering a range of themes including education, health, vocational training and peace-building. They work to build the capacity of partners, helping to assess need and share experience and good practice through workshops and publications. This project will equip Feed the Minds and their growing number of partners with an upgraded web-based platform through which this dialogue can be significantly extended and improved. This will enable new opportunities for partners to share and learn, through appropriate and accessible technology suited to a range of literacy levels such as webinars, videos, shared databases, documentation and discussion forums. Reporting, monitoring and evaluation will also be strengthened as a result of the improved systems. At the same time, the new website will enable more efficient and effective communications with UK donors and supporters &#xE2;&#x20AC;&#x201C; increasing their profile and fundraising revenues to sustain and build programmes.</narrative>
  </description>
